In Python - Function is different. Method is different.

Function is a set of statments which 'll perform a task.
      Function declaration
      Calling(Invoking) a Function
      
 A Function can be called 'n' no.of.times.
      
There are 2 types of Functions,
  Built - in Function
  User defined Function.
  
Syntax: (Indentation is must)
      def functionname():
            body of the function
            
      # To call Function    
      functionname()

1) Function without Parameter
2) Function with Parameter
3) Function with Multiple Parameter -> return statement

2 Types of Arguments/Parameters can passed to the Function:
1) Positional Arguments
2) Keyword Arguments


